title: Ayn Rand - The Fountainhead
description: The Fountainhead is a 1943 novel by Ayn Rand. It was Rand&#039;s first major literary success and its royalties and movie rights brought her fame and financial security. The book&#039;s title is a reference to Rand&#039;s statement that "man&#039;s ego is the fountainhead of human progress," and is a more specific version of the book&#039;s theme, which is, in Rand&#039;s words, "individualism and collectivism in man&#039;s soul."
